--- SOURCE 3: 万华化学(600309.SH)研究报告-PC_HSF10资料 ---
URL: http://emweb.securities.eastmoney.com/pc_hsf10/ResearchReport/index?code=SH600309

SUMMARY:
<summary>
The webpage contains multiple analyst reports on Wanhua Chemical (stock code 600309) discussing its Q3 2025 financial results, released on October 24-25, 2025. For the first three quarters of 2025 (Q1-Q3), the company reported a slight year-on-year revenue decline of 2.3% to approximately 1,442.3 billion RMB, with a more significant drop in net profit attributable to shareholders of 17.5% to about 91.6 billion RMB. However, performance improved in Q3 2025 alone, with revenue reaching 533.2 billion RMB (up 5.5% year-on-year and 11.5% quarter-on-quarter) and net profit attributable to shareholders at 30.3 billion RMB (up 4.0% year-on-year but down 0.2% quarter-on-quarter). Analysts highlight that the Q3 results showed stability, meeting expectations, and indicate a potential industry recovery. Key operational highlights include growth in the polyurethane series (551.43 billion RMB in sales for the first three quarters), capacity expansion in new materials, and ongoing plant upgrades, such as the retrofit of the first ethylene unit to use ethane feedstock, which is expected to significantly reduce production costs. The overall sentiment is cautiously optimistic, with several reports maintaining a 'buy' rating, citing the company's long-term growth prospects amidst a tightening TDI supply-demand dynamic and rising prices.
</summary>

<key_excerpts>
2025前三季度实现营业总收入1442.3亿元，同比-2.3%；归母净利润91.6亿元，同比-17.5%, 2025Q3实现营业总收入533.2亿元，同环比分别+5.5%/+11.5%;归母净利润为30.3亿元，同环比分别+4.0%/-0.2%, 公司Q3业绩环比基本稳定，看好公司未来长期成长，维持“买入”评级, TDI供需趋紧价格上涨，聚氨酯及新材料产能逐步落地, 第一套乙烯装置改造完成后预计显著降低生产成本
