URL: https://quote.cfi.cn/ybdata.aspx?id=20251114000184

SUMMARY:
<summary>
On October 24, 2025, Wanhua Chemical released its Q3 2025 financial results. For the first three quarters of 2025, revenue was 1442.26 billion yuan (down 2.29% year-on-year), with net profit attributable to shareholders at 91.57 billion yuan (down 17.45%). The company's performance was pressured by declining selling prices for its main products, despite increased production volumes across its core segments: fine chemicals & new materials, polyurethane, and petrochemicals. The report details specific price changes for key products and raw materials in Q3. Several new production facilities were successfully commissioned during the period, and the company is advancing its diversified product strategy in areas like optical materials, battery materials, and engineering plastics. Analysts from Great Wall Securities maintain a 'buy' rating, forecasting revenue and profit growth from 2026 onward, citing the company's expanding product portfolio as a key competitive strength.
