SUMMARY:
<summary>
On February 27, 2026, Chinese authorities announced a series of major policy measures aimed at stabilizing and stimulating the economy, providing a strong signal to the A-share market. The core announcement came from a Politburo meeting, setting the tone for 2026 and the 15th Five-Year Plan (2026-2030), pledging continued proactive fiscal policy and moderately easy monetary policy to boost the domestic market, technological innovation, and reform. Key concrete measures included the central bank lowering the foreign exchange risk reserve ratio for forward sales from 20% to 0, effective March 2, to reduce hedging costs for import/export firms. Additionally, the Tariff Commission announced the removal of retaliatory tariffs on certain Canadian goods, including oilseed cake and peas (100% tariff) and lobster and crab (25% tariff), effective March 1.
</summary>

<key_excerpts>
继续实施积极的财政政策和适度宽松的货币政策，重点抓“强大国内市场、科技创新、改革开放”。, 远期售汇业务的外汇风险准备金率从20%降到0。, 对加拿大的油渣饼、豌豆不再加征100%关税，龙虾、蟹不再加征25%关税。
