--- SOURCE 4: 2026两会前瞻 | 开局之年，宏观政策如何定调? ---
URL: http://www.ce.cn/xwzx/gnsz/gdxw/202602/t20260228_2793355.shtml

SUMMARY:
<summary>
This article, published on February 28, 2026, is a preview of China's macroeconomic policy direction for 2026, as the "15th Five-Year Plan" ("十五五") begins. It reports that economists expect policies to focus on achieving a strong economic start in Q1 ("开门红") through proactive and coordinated fiscal and monetary measures. Fiscal policy is anticipated to be continuous and stable, with general public budget expenditure potentially exceeding 30 trillion yuan and a budget deficit rate around 4%. Monetary policy is expected to include a 50 basis point reserve requirement ratio (RRR) cut in Q1 and one interest rate cut of 10-20 basis points for the year to support government debt issuance. Expanding domestic demand is identified as the top priority, with a focus on increasing household income ("居民增收") and "investing in people" ("投资于人") to boost consumption and find new investment growth areas. Emerging consumption trends like "谷子经济" and "国潮经济" are noted.
</summary>

<key_excerpts>
要确保2026年经济运行继续保持在合理区间，并为“十五五”开局夯实基础，宏观政策有必要适度加码、形成合力。, 我们预计2026年‘一本账’预算支出有望超过30万亿元，预算赤字率或保持在4%左右，政府债务发行总量再创新高。, 降准、降息仍有空间...50BP的降准有望在一季度落地；预计全年会有1次降息，总计调降政策利率10-20BP。, 扩大内需是今年经济工作的头号任务。, “居民增收”和“投资于人”将是扩大内需、增强经济内生动能的重要抓手。
</key_excerpts>



