--- SOURCE 20: 从政策驱动到市场驱动:退税取消撬动光伏行业转型 ---
URL: https://www.koyoe.com/newshow.asp?Id=121

SUMMARY:
<summary>
On January 9, 2026, China's Ministry of Finance and State Taxation Administration announced a major policy shift, phasing out the 13-year export tax rebate for the photovoltaic industry. From April 1, 2026, the VAT export rebate will be canceled for 249 items including silicon wafers, cells, and modules. Battery products have a transition period, with the rebate reduced from 9% to 6% from April 1 to December 31, 2026, before full cancellation on January 1, 2027. This marks the industry's shift from policy-driven to market-driven development.

Key impacts by sector:
- **Battery Sector**: SMM estimates companies will lose 10-20 billion yuan annually in rebates, reducing profit per 210R cell by 46-51 yuan. This pressures small and medium-sized enterprises (SMEs), while leaders like CATL and BYD can leverage overseas production and pricing power. The change will accelerate industry consolidation.
- **Inverter Sector**: Inverters are largely unaffected, constituting a direct benefit. However, indirect risks exist from potential project delays or cost pressures from overseas clients. Leaders like Sungrow and Ginlong can manage through innovation and overseas capacity.
- **Component Sector**: SMM estimates component makers will also lose 10-20 billion yuan annually, with profit per 210R module reduced by 46-51 yuan. An export surge is expected before April 2026, benefiting logistics. Leaders like LONGi and JinkoSolar can adapt via overseas capacity and premium pricing.

Overall, the policy will drive the entire industry towards technological innovation and higher value-added products, accelerating the shift from low-price competition to high-quality development, while further consolidating market share among leading firms with overseas production.
</summary>

<key_excerpts>
2026年1月9日，财政部和税务总局联合发布公告，对光伏及电池产品出口退税政策作出重大调整，标志着光伏行业彻底告别长达13年的出口退税时代，行业发展将从政策驱动正式转向市场驱动。, 据SMM（上海有色网）测算，政策全面落地后，电池企业每年预计减少10-20亿元退税款，对应每块210R电池出口利润将减少46-51元。, 此次政策调整将加速电池行业优胜劣汰，进一步提升头部企业市场份额，推动行业从低价竞争向高质量发展转型，倒逼企业强化技术创新、提高产品附加值。, 逆变器等核心设备因不被归入“光伏组件”或“电池”原材范畴，其出口退税政策大概率维持不变，或受影响程度远低于组件环节，这对逆变器企业构成显著利好。, 从长期来看，政策将推动全行业强化技术创新、提高产品附加值，加速从低价竞争向高质量发展转型；头部企业将进一步加快海外产能布局，既规避出口退税限制与贸易壁垒，也将凭借优势扩大市场份额，推动行业集中度持续提升。
</key_excerpts>



