<summary>
The webpage presents a series of earnings forecasts for Wanhua Chemical (stock code 600309), detailing its financial performance from 2021 to 2024. The key information includes stock price data and annual performance previews showing fluctuating profitability. For the forecast period ending December 31, 2024, the company expects a net profit attributable to shareholders of 1,303,306.66 million RMB, a decrease of 22.49% year-over-year, due to cost pressures, increased expenses, and asset impairment provisions, despite a 3.83% revenue growth to 18,206,911.92 million RMB. In contrast, 2023 saw a 3.57% profit increase to 1,681,389.13 million RMB. The year 2022 experienced a 34.12% profit decline to 1,623,933.32 million RMB, attributed to rising global raw material and energy costs outpacing revenue growth. The year 2021 marked a significant surge with a 145.47% profit increase to 2,464,874.81 million RMB, driven by post-pandemic demand recovery, supply chain disruptions leading to higher product prices, and new production capacities. A mid-2021 forecast also indicated a 380% profit growth. The reports consistently explain the factors behind these changes, including market conditions, operational expansions, and cost management.
</summary>

<key_excerpts>
