URL: https://m.thepaper.cn/newsDetail_forward_31859306

SUMMARY:
<summary>
On October 31, 2025, at its third-quarter earnings conference, China Merchants Bank (CMB) described the current risk status of its real estate sector as characterized by three trends: stable and declining scale, improving structure, and stabilizing asset quality. Specifically, the proportion of real estate loans in CMB's corporate loans has fallen from 19% in 2019-2020 to 9.88% as of the end of September 2025. The structure has improved, with over 85% of its real estate development loan balance concentrated in urban areas of first- and second-tier cities, and its top ten real estate group exposures (over 70% of which are state-owned enterprises) accounting for nearly 40% of its total real estate loan portfolio. The non-performing loan (NPL) ratio for real estate was 4.24% at the end of September, down 0.5 percentage points from the end of the previous year, with provisions set at 2.5 to 3 times the corporate average. For its personal housing loans, the NPL ratio was 0.45%, slightly down from 0.48% at year-end 2024. The bank stated its future strategy involves selecting optimal regions, clients, and projects to balance asset quality and business development. It acknowledged that while current asset disposal measures keep mortgage risks controllable, the overall risk trend for its mortgage business is expected to continue rising modestly in the near term.
</summary>

<key_excerpts>
一是规模稳中有降，二是结构有所好转，三是质量趋于稳定。, 85%以上的房地产开发贷款余额分布在一、二线城市城区；二是招行前十大房地产集团业务在招行整个房地产贷款的规模里占比接近4成，其中国企占比超过7成。, 9月末招行房地产不良率是4.24%，较上年末下降0.5个百分点, 招行房地产贷款是逐笔分类计提拨备，拨备的水平是相当于对公平均计提水平的2.5倍到3倍, 招行房贷业务的风险还会呈现一个小幅上行的趋势。
</key_excerpts>



