URL: https://finance.sina.com.cn/stock/relnews/cn/2025-03-26/doc-ineqyzve4615085.shtml

SUMMARY:
<summary>
An article from the Shanghai Securities News on March 26, 2025, analyzes the 2024 annual report of China Merchants Bank (CMB), highlighting the pressures faced by the leading retail bank despite overall stable performance. While the bank's operations were characterized as 'steady, progressive, and good' with a net profit increase to 1483.91 billion yuan, key challenges emerged. The net interest margin fell below 2% to 1.98%, pressured by loan repricing and deposit terming trends. Its flagship 'Big Wealth Management' business saw revenue decline by 16.84% to 376.47 billion yuan, though overall non-interest income grew slightly. Asset quality remained robust with a non-performing loan ratio of 0.95%, and exposure to real estate risks decreased. The bank announced a high dividend payout of 504.40 billion yuan, representing a 35.32% payout ratio.
</summary>

<key_excerpts>
息差仍未企稳，跌破了2%；存款定期化仍在延续；引以为傲的大财富管理业务，收入仍在下降。, 招行2024年大财富管理收入376.47亿元，同比下降16.84%，并且下降速度超过2023年的7.9%。, 报告期末，该行拨备覆盖率411.98%，较上年末下降25.72个百分点。, 该行拟分红总额为504.40亿元，分红比例达35.32%，略高于2023年。
