--- SOURCE 1: 中际旭创业绩快报:2025年归母净利润同比增长108.81% ---
URL: https://new.qq.com/rain/a/20260228A05HKA00

SUMMARY:
<summary>
On February 27, 2025, the leading optical module manufacturer Zhongji Innolight (中际旭创) released its 2025 annual performance forecast. The report showed substantial growth: full-year operating revenue reached 382.4 billion yuan, a 60.25% increase from 2024, while net profit attributable to shareholders was 107.99 billion yuan, surging 108.81% year-over-year. The company attributed this strong performance to robust customer investment in computing infrastructure, leading to rapid shipment growth, especially for high-speed optical modules, alongside optimized product solutions and improved operational efficiency. The optical module business alone achieved a net profit of approximately 117.64 billion yuan, which would be 119.86 billion yuan after adjusting for share-based compensation expenses, a significant rise from about 56.6 billion yuan in 2024. The company's total assets also grew to 455.3 billion yuan by the end of 2025, a 57.72% increase from the beginning of the period. In the secondary market, its stock price closed at 534 yuan per share on February 27, down 6.68% for the day.
